description:
New app: apps/mobile (@vex-chat/mobile). Bare React Native — no Expo SDK.

(0) ROOT .npmrc: Add node-linker=hoisted to the repo root .npmrc. This makes pnpm produce a flat node_modules so Metro, Gradle, and CocoaPods all work without symlink gymnastics.

(1) SCAFFOLD: Run npx react-native@latest init from apps/mobile/ (or init to a temp dir and move). Rename package.json#name to @vex-chat/mobile. Keep existing tsconfig.json and src/store/index.ts.

(2) METRO: Create apps/mobile/metro.config.js:
    const path = require('path')
    const { getDefaultConfig, mergeConfig } = require('@react-native/metro-config')
    const projectRoot = __dirname
    const workspaceRoot = path.resolve(projectRoot, '../..')
    module.exports = mergeConfig(getDefaultConfig(projectRoot), {
      watchFolders: [workspaceRoot],
      resolver: {
        unstable_enableSymlinks: true,
        unstable_enablePackageExports: true,
        nodeModulesPaths: [
          path.resolve(projectRoot, 'node_modules'),
          path.resolve(workspaceRoot, 'node_modules'),
        ],
      },
    })

(3) REACT NATIVE CONFIG: Create apps/mobile/react-native.config.js:
    module.exports = { reactNativePath: '../../node_modules/react-native' }
    Required because app is nested; CLI otherwise can't find react-native.

(4) ANDROID GRADLE PATHS: After init, adjust all '../node_modules/' paths in android/settings.gradle and android/app/build.gradle to '../../../node_modules/' to account for nesting inside apps/mobile/.

(5) IOS PODFILE PATHS: Similarly update ios/Podfile require_relative paths from '../node_modules/' to '../../../node_modules/'. Run pod install.

(6) NAVIGATION: install @react-navigation/native + @react-navigation/native-stack + @react-navigation/bottom-tabs. Set up root Stack navigator with two stacks:
    - Auth stack: Login, Register screens
    - App stack: DM list, Server/Channel view, Settings

(7) STORE WIRING: Call bootstrap(serverUrl, deviceID, deviceKey) from @vex-chat/store in App.tsx root useEffect. nanostores atoms are module-level singletons — no React context needed. Handle $keyReplaced to redirect to Login.

(8) WORKSPACE DEPS: @vex-chat/store (workspace:*), @vex-chat/types (workspace:*), @vex-chat/ui (workspace:*) [from output/react/], @nanostores/react (catalog:).

Platform: React Native renders actual native views (iOS UIKit + Android Views). Build with Xcode (iOS) or Gradle (Android). See docs/react-native-monorepo.md for full setup reference.
